webHelper_successMsg()

Description
    string webHelper_successMsg(string $message)
    Builds a success message with the proper markup for display.

Parameters
    message
        A string value containing the text of the success message.

Return Values
    Returns a string value containing the success message with the appropriate markup.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	if(empty($output)) {
	    $output = webHelper_successMsg("Database successfully updated.");
	}
	...
    ?>

See Also
    webHelper_errorMsg()
